  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Karandeep Sharma @ Razia @ Raju versus State of Uttarakhand pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_3_1482_1502','2025INSC444'); ><font size='4'> <strong>KARANDEEP SHARMA @ RAZIA @ RAJU<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF UTTARAKHAND </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 3 S.C.R. 1482</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 444</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004752025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANJAY KAROL, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration In a case based on circumstantial evidence, whether the concurrent conviction of the appellant-accused for the kidnapping, rape/sexual assault and murder of a minor is sustainable. Headnotes&dagger; Circumstantial evidence &ndash; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; ss.376A, &ndash; Protection of Children from Sexual Offences Act, 2012 &ndash; ss.5, 6 &ndash; Kidnapping, rape/sexual assault and murder of minor &ndash; Case based on circumstantial evidence &ndash; Appellant was convicted, death sentence awarded &ndash; Sustainability: Held: Unsustainable &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 04-03-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 630/2018</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 3 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_3_1482_1502','2025INSC444','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a